{
  "texts": [
    "F1 is the harmonic mean of precision and recall.",
    "An F1 value of one means that the model correctly classifies all classes; zero means all samples are wrongly classified.",
    "The F1 score requires converting the account credibility scores provided by the algorithms into binary labels using a threshold.",
    "We calculate precision and recall for a thousand threshold values spanning the unit interval and select the optimal threshold that maximizes the F1 score.",
    "Since NewsGuard ratings are available for only a subset of domains shared in a dataset, we assign a label confidence score to an account by calculating the fraction of known domains that they shared; this number is between zero and one."
  ]
}